<h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Sessions</h1>

<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-6">
  Sessions are the PTY processes managed by Botster. There are two types:
  <strong class="text-zinc-200">agents</strong> (AI-driven, e.g., Claude) and
  <strong class="text-zinc-200">accessories</strong> (plain PTYs, e.g., dev servers).
  Each session definition owns a directory, and each running session starts one PTY from that definition.
</p>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Agents</h2>
<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-4">
  Agent definitions live in <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">agents/</code>.
  At least one agent config is required. The <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">initialization</code>
  script is the entry point; any other files in the directory are owned by that agent definition.
</p>
<pre class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300 font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code># .botster/agents/claude/initialization
#!/bin/bash
EXTRA_ARGS=()
if notes="$(botster context file notes.md 2>/dev/null)"; then
  EXTRA_ARGS+=(--append-system-prompt "$notes")
fi

claude "${EXTRA_ARGS[@]}" --dangerously-skip-permissions</code></pre>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Accessories</h2>
<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-4">
  Accessory definitions live in <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">accessories/</code>.
  They're plain PTY sessions without AI autonomy &mdash; dev servers, log tailers, port forwarders.
</p>
<pre class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300 font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code># .botster/accessories/rails-server/initialization
#!/bin/bash
bin/dev</code></pre>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Port forwarding</h2>
<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-4">
  To enable port forwarding for a session, create a
  <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">port_forward</code> sentinel
  file next to the initialization script. This makes the session's port accessible via the preview UI
  and sets the <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">$PORT</code> environment variable.
</p>
<pre class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300 font-mono overflow-x-auto"><code>accessories/rails-server/
  initialization     # Startup script
  port_forward       # Empty file - enables port forwarding</code></pre>
